Subject: 1965 European Amateur Boxing Championships 
To: Margaret
Content:
The 1965 European Amateur Boxing Championships were held in East Berlin, East Germany from 22 to 29 May. The 16th edition of the bi-annual competition was organised by the European governing body for amateur boxing, EABA. There were 172 fighters from 24 countries participating. Scotland John McCluskey Scotland West Germany Horst Rascher West Germany East Germany Wolfgang Hbner East Germany Romania Antoniu Vasile Romania Austria Rupert Knig Austria Czechoslovakia Vladimr Kuera Czechoslovakia Austria Anton Schnedl Austria East Germany Wolfgang Trodler East Germany Hungary Bla Horvth Hungary Hungary Ern Sznsi Hungary Host nation (East Germany)
I read the paragraph on http://wikipedia.org
